data-triple-N3.o: "Vatican City Listen/ˈvaetikən ˈsɪti/, or Vatican City State, in Italian officially Stato della Citta del Vaticano, is a landlocked sovereign city-state whose territory consists of a walled enclave within the city of Rome. It has an area of approximately 44 hectares, and a population of just over 800. This makes Vatican City the smallest internationally recognized independent state in the world by both area and population."@en
